title: Frieze, 1905–15
description: Alternating tulip and stems: two large tulips, one small tulip, one large tulip, and one small tulip. The large tulips have large leaves and stamen. Bottom and top both have scroll panels with a pink background. Bottom also has square beading. Secondary layer of stem and tulip motif in background, over an overall vertical green dash pattern. Ungrounded. Printed in pinks, green, browns, and beige.

tombstone.epitaph:
Frieze, 1905–15.
1905–15. Machine-printed on paper. Gift of Victorian Collectibles. 1979-91-541.
